<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader Hopes for Increased Sino-German Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, Germany, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of
the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference, hoped the cooperation and exchanges
between the German state of Brandenburg and China's provinces and
cities will further develop.
</P>
<P>
While meeting Manfred Stolpe, premier of Brandenburg state in
Potsdam, capital of Brandenburg, Li spoke highly of Brandenburg
for its important role in Germany's politics and economy and its
increasingly entensive cooperation with Chinese enterprises.
</P>
<P>
He said that China has great interest in broader cooperation
with Brandenburg.
</P>
<P>
Stolpe said he was deeply impressed by the rapid economic
development of China during his recent Chinese trip, adding that
in the 21st century the world should pay more attention to China's
views.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China and eastern Germany have many points in
common with regard to their ongoing economic reforms, therefore,
the cooperation between the two sides should be further
strengthened.
</P>
<P>
Earlier today, the Chinese leader visited the Adtranz GmbH, a
major railway systems provider, in Henningsdorf of Brandenburg.
</P>
<P>
The company is producing the rolling stock for the subway
project in the southern Chinese city of Guangzhou. 
</P>
</TEXT>
