<HEADLINE> Gotti Wins Tour of Italy Cycling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Italian Ivan Gotti won the Tour of
Italy cycling race following the 22nd and final stage in Milan on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old became the first Italian winner of the race in
six years, finishing ahead of Russia's Pavel Tonkov in the
overall standings.
</P>
<P>
Italian Mario Cipollini won Sunday's final stage. 
</P>
