<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arafat in Jordan for Talks on Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, June 8 (Xinhua) -- President of Palestinian National
Authority Yasser Arafat arrived here this evening and held talks
with King Hussein on the stalled Middle East peace.
</P>
<P>
Both sides discussed issues of mutual concern during the
meeting which was also attended by Jordanian Prime Minister Abdul
Salam Majali, Radio Jordan reported. No details of the talks
are available.
</P>
<P>
Jordan is one of the important mediators in the peace talks and
successfully brokered the Hebron accord in January, under which
Israel agreed to withdraw troops from the West Bank.
</P>
<P>
However, the Middle East peace process was deadlocked again in
March when Israel decided to build Jewish settlements in Arab East
Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
In recent days, Israel and the Palestinians have expressed
the wish to meet again on the peace process and Arafat met
Mubarak in Cairo yesterday on relevant issues. 
</P>
</TEXT>
