<HEADLINE> Iran Voices Concern over Turkish Presence in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Iran today voiced its concern over
the presence by Turkish military forces in northern Iraq, saying
it is "sensitive" to Iraqi territorial integrity.
</P>
<P>
Iranian Deputy Foreign Minister Alaeddin Bourujerdi told
reporters here that Iran gave importance to security of the
regional states and understood the Turkish security problems.
</P>
<P>
But, he noted that the move taken by Turkey is not the solution
to the problem.
</P>
<P>
About 50,000 Turkish government troops have carried out
cross-border military operations in northern Iraq since May 14 to
destroy the establishment of the outlawed Kurdish Workers Party
(PKK) there.
</P>
<P>
Bourujerdi urged Turkey to immediately bring the current
operations in northern Iraq to an end.
</P>
<P>
He said Turkey is required to solve its security problem in
cooperation with the regional Islamic states.
</P>
<P>
Bourujerdi said consultations already underway between Iran
and Turkey on the developments in northern Iraq were useful and
Iran believes that such cooperation should continue.
</P>
<P>
Elaborating on the Iranian diplomacy, Bourujerdi stressed that
Iran will continue to strictly follow its policy of not
allowing the presence of the PKK forces on the Iranian soil.
</P>
</TEXT>
