<HEADLINE> Ireland's Ahern to Seek Peace Talks with Sinn Fein </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Bertie Ahern, who is set to become
Ireland's new Prime Minister, has promised to discuss with Sinn
Fein, the political wing of the Irish Republican Army (IRA),
Northern Ireland peace process.
</P>
<P>
Ahern, whose opposition Fianna Fail-Progressive Democrats
alliance just won a narrow victory in the general election, was
quoted by press reports from Dublin as saying that he expected to
have contacts with Sinn Fein leader Gerry Adams this week.
</P>
<P>
"I would say I would have contact with Gerry Adams over the
next week if this is possible,'' Ahern said, adding that the
Northern Ireland conflict would be a top priority for the next
government.
</P>
<P>
On the future of the Northern Ireland issue, Ahern expressed
optimistic views on forging a settlement to the 28-year conflict
over Northern Ireland by saying "The possibilities of moving
forward are tremendous."
</P>
<P>
The British and Irish governments, which had refused to allow
Sinn Fein to attend the all-party talks on the future of Northern
Ireland since last February, have recently reopened contacts with
Sinn Fein in a bid to give a fresh impetus to the Northern Ireland
peace process. 
</P>
