<HEADLINE> Jet Swerves to Avoid Collision </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Eighty-one people aboard a
Chicago-bound United Airlines jet got a scare Sunday morning when
their Boeing 737 pulled up abruptly, apparently to avoid another
aircraft.
</P>
<P>
A United Airlines spokesman said the pilot of Flight 1517 from
Philadelphia was descending on approach into Chicago's O'Hare
International Airport at about 9:30 a.m. local time when he got a
warning from his aircraft's collision avoidance system, The United
Press International reported.
</P>
<P>
The pilot saw what he described as a Cessna airplane nearby and
took evasive action, steering the jet into an abrupt upward turn.
</P>
<P>
Two flight attendants were bumped around inside and sustained
minor injuries.
</P>
<P>
The jet carrying 76 passengers and five crew members later
landed normally at O'Hare.  
</P>
