<HEADLINE> EU Provides Medical Aid to Nicaragua </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission announced
on Monday that it had approved emergency medical aid worth 2.8
million ECUs (3.2 million U.S. dollars) for Nicaragua.
</P>
<P>
The aid, managed by the European Community Humanitarian Office
(ECHO), will enable European non-governmental organizations to
carry out a nine-month program to control epidemics in the Central
American country.
</P>
<P>
The Commission said the grant would finance supplying basic
medicines and medical supplies for treatment and prevention,
organizing training and preventive campaigns, and providing basic
sanitation and clean drinking water.
</P>
<P>
Official statistics show the cases of malaria in Nicaragua have
doubled over the past five years, while those of cholera have
tripled.
</P>
<P>
Nearly half the country's population of 4.3 million has no
access to clean drinking water. In rural areas, more than 70
percent do not have basic sanitation facilities.
</P>
<P>
The EU aid is expected to benefit more than two million
people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
