<HEADLINE> Sino-Macedonian Officials Discuss Bilateral Relations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The formal meeting between the
Chinese and Macedonian heads of state here has ushered in "a new
phase in the development of the Sino-Macedonian ties,"
Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo said today.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with Macedonia's Deputy Prime Minister Zlatka
Popovska, Wu called President Kiro Gligorov's current China visit
"an important event" in bilateral relations, and said China
believes that it will greatly increase mutual understanding,
strengthen cooperation, and promote the development of bilateral
relations.
</P>
<P>
Popovska said that China is a great country and has had many
achievements in recent years, and that Macedonia is China's
traditional friend and is willing to conduct friendly cooperation
with in the economy, foreign trade and technology.
</P>
<P>
She said she believes that the Macedonian president's visit
will contribute to faster growth in Macedonian-Chinese relations.
</P>
<P>
Economic and trade relations are an important part of bilateral
ties, Wu noted, adding that the Chinese Government pays great
attention to economic relations with Macedonia and hopes that the
two countries will seize the opportunity and increase economic
cooperation by increasing their understanding of each other and
adopting positive measures.
</P>
<P>
The two officials discussed the development of Sino-Macedonian
economic and trade relations and said they both believe that there
are many areas for cooperation, and that there are good prospects
for economic ties. 
</P>
