<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Macedonian Presidents  (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gligorov said that Taiwan is a part of China and that the
Taiwan issue is an internal matter for China. Macedonia backs
China's position on Taiwan and supports its reunification efforts,
he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang stressed that China does not pursue any interest of its
own in the the former Yugoslavian region, and always believes that
disputes between the countries in the region should be solved with
a peaceful approach.
</P>
<P>
The countries in the region are China's friends, Jiang said,
adding that he hopes the parties involved will handle the problems
through patient negotiations so as to become good neighbors.
</P>
<P>
This is in the fundamental interest of the people of the region
and conducive to European and world peace and stability, he said.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the world is moving toward multi-polarization since
the end of the Cold War, Gligorov believed that all countries have
a responsibility in maintaining world peace, and that his country
is happy to see that China is playing an increasingly important
role on the international scene.
</P>
<P>
Jiang stressed that the multi-polarization of the world helps
developing countries and small and medium-sized nations to have an
independent role in international affairs.
</P>
<P>
"We stand for a new international political and economic order
that is fair and reasonable should be built on the basis of the
Five Principles of Peaceful Co-existence and other universally
acknowledged norms governing international relations."
</P>
<P>
China and Macedonia share similar views on many major
international issues, Jiang said, and that China is ready to
strengthen consultation and cooperation with Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
After the talks, the two presidents signed a joint communique
between China and Macedonia, and attended the signing ceremony for
an agreement between the Chinese and Macedonian governments on
reciprocal protection of investment, an agreement on avoiding
double taxation and the prevention of evasion of income and
capital taxes, a cultural cooperation plan from 1997 to 1999, and
an agreement of cooperation between the China Chamber of
International Trade and the Economic Chamber of Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
</P>
