<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese, Macedonian Presidents Hold Talks (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin, in talks
with Macedonian President Kiro Gligorov this afternoon, said that
Gligorov's visit will strengthen the friendship between the two
governments and peoples and will raise Sino-Macedonian relations
to a new level.
</P>
<P>
China and Macedonia have a tradition of friendship, Jiang
noted, and bilateral relations have achieved many things since
diplomatic ties were opened in 1993. The two countries' leaders
have frequent contacts, the two sides have deepened their
cooperation in politics, the economy, education and the media, and
have been supporting each other in international affairs, he said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang attributed the development of bilateral friendly
relations to two things: Both sides strictly abide by the
principles of mutual respect, equality, mutual benefit and
non-interference in each other's internal affairs; and there is no
conflict of interest between the two countries and developing
relations is in the fundamental interests of the two governments
and peoples.
</P>
<P>
Jiang called Macedonia an important country in the Balkan
region and said that China places great importance on developing
relations with it, and respects its independence, territorial
integrity, and sovereignty, and its people's choice of development
road and domestic and foreign policies in relation to their own
national situation.
</P>
<P>
He said that China is ready to further its relations with
Macedonia on the basis of the Five Principles of Peaceful
Coexistence.
</P>
<P>
Gligorov said there have been frequent high-level visits since
diplomatic relations were opened, and that there is still great
potential to develop friendship between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Macedonia and China share similar views on international
affairs and both countries are making an effort to safeguard world
peace and international cooperation, he noted.
</P>
<P>
He thanked China, which is a permanent member of the UN
Security Council, for its support to Macedonia in international
affairs.
</P>
<P>
In order to promote bilateral trade and economic relations,
Jiang said, both sides should encourage companies and regions to
have more understanding and contacts with their counterparts,
cooperate in various ways and encourage the various departments to
play a bigger role.
</P>
<P>
On the occasion of Hong Kong's forthcoming return to the
motherland, Gligorov said he wanted to express his best wishes to
the Chinese government and people and wish Hong Kong a stable and
prosperous future.
</P>
</TEXT>
