<HEADLINE> Shoe-making and Leather Equipment on Show in Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 9 (Xinhua) -- An international exhibition of
equipment used in shoe and leather production opened today in
Guangzhou, the capital of south China's Guangdong Province.
</P>
<P>
About 400 shoe manufacturers from China's inland areas, Hong
Kong, Taiwan, and foreign countries had many of their new products
on display. Famous Italian and German manufacturers were present.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong has become an important production and export center
for Chinese shoes, with the greatest production, sales, and export
volume of any province or autonomous region.
</P>
<P>
It produced more than 1.3 billion pairs of shoes in 1996, and
had 3.2 billion US dollars worth of exports, up 18.5 percent from
1995.
</P>
<P>
But it has still not produced any internationally famous brand
of shoes.
</P>
<P>
It is hoped that the four-day exhibition will help the province
improve the quality of its shoes and help it catch up with
international trends. 
</P>
</TEXT>
