<HEADLINE> Syria Beats Maldives 12-0 in World Cup qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June, 9 (Xinhua) -- Syria overpowered Maldives 12-0
in a World Cup Asian zone soccer qualifying match on Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Syrians scored only one goal in the first half through Agha
Arif, but turned the second half to a scoring spree.
</P>
<P>
Arif and teammate Saeed Bayazdal each picked up a hat-trick
while Radwan Abrash grabbed two and Taleb Louay, Ali Deeb and
Taher Khaled each scored one as the Syrians dominated the Group 2
game in front of 15,000 spectators.
</P>
<P>
Iran and Kyrgyzstan, the other teams in the group, were
scheduled to meet later Monday. Only the first-round group winners
advance to the second round. 
</P>
