<HEADLINE> Iraqi President's Eldest Son Recovered From </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BAGHDAD, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Iraqi President Saddam Hussein's
eldest son Uday Hussein has completely recovered from injuries by
unidentified gunmen, the Iraqi News Agency (INA) reported today.
</P>
<P>
Uday left Ibn Sina Hospital in Baghdad this afternoon,
according to INA.
</P>
<P>
Uday, 33, who has been widely believed to be President
Saddam's heir, was shot about 10 times while waiting alone in a
car in a Baghdad suburb on the evening of December 12.
</P>
<P>
Iraq accused Iran of carrying out the attack, but Tehran
denied the charge.
</P>
<P>
Uday recovered after a bullet was removed from his spine last
month in a successful operation carried out by French and Iraqi
doctors. 
</P>
