<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Five ASIAN TV Stations Produce Five-Part Documentary on Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 9 (Xinhua) -- A five-part documentary produced
by five Asian TV stations gives a picture of Hong Kong from the
viewpoint of its neighbors.
</P>
<P>
The documentary shows Hong Kong's relations with Shanghai,
Japan, the Republic of Korea (ROK), Singapore, as well as its
importance to Asia, through interviewing business people, bankers,
entrepreneurs, and economists.
</P>
<P>
TV stations of Shanghai, Hong Kong, Japan, the ROK, and
Singapore each produced a 30-minute segment, under the headings
"New milestone for Hong Kong", "Competition Continues"
(Singapore), "Tomorrow's Sun" (ROK), "Hong Kong Strategy of
Japanese Banks" (Japan), and "Shanghai and Hong Kong in 1997"
(Shanghai).
</P>
<P>
The documentary, which is being shown, expresses an idea held
by many Asian people that the five places will have new
opportunities and challenges and that Hong Kong has a bright
future. 
</P>
</TEXT>
