<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Albanian PM to Visit Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Albanian Prime Minister Bashkim
Fino is to pay a two-day official visit to Turkey on June 11-12
in a bid to enhance Albanian-Turkish ties.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a weekly news briefing, Turkish Foreign Ministry
Spokesman Omel Akbel said that bilateral relations and regional
issues would be discussed during the visit.
</P>
<P>
During his visit to Ankara, Fino is expected to meet Islamic
Turkish Prime Minister Necmettin Erbakan and other Turkish
officials.
</P>
<P>
The return of Turkish businessmen who fled from
chaos-stricken Albania, the increase of Turkey's investments as
well as logistic assistance to Albanian army and police will
also be on the agenda, local media reports said.
</P>
<P>
Fino's visit to Ankara aims to ask for economic help from
Turkey, according to informed sources.
</P>
<P>
Asked whether Turkey plans to extend the time limit of its
troops stationed in Albania, Akbel said that Turkey has not made
a decision in this regard, adding that other countries
participating in the mission were also considering this issue.
</P>
<P>
The Albanian government has reportedly asked the Italy-led
multinational peacekeeping force to extend its time limit for
another three months.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Akbel said that Turkey had been making efforts
to help restore peace and stability in that country.
</P>
<P>
Turkey has decided to provide a 50-million-dollar aid to
Albania in a bid to help the country overcome its current
economic difficulties.
</P>
<P>
At present, Turkey has 850 troops in Albania, as part of
the 6,000-strong multinational peacekeeping troops stationed there
to help local army and police to keep order. 
</P>
</TEXT>
