Turkey, carrying a message from Iranian President Hashemi
Rafsanjani concerning ties between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
The semi-official Anatolia News Agency said that Bourujerdi
will present Ransanjani's message to Turkish President Suleyman
Demirel Tuesday, and he has no plan to meet with other Turkish
high-ranking officials during his visit here
</P>
<P>
Turkish military accused Iran of providing support for the
outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK), which has been fighting an
almost 13-year-old separatist war for autonomy in eastern and
southeastern Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Bourujerdi told reporters in Tehran Sunday that Iran voiced
its concern over the presence by Turkish military forces in
northern Iraq, saying it is "sensitive" to Iraqi territorial
integrity.
</P>
<P>
He said that Iran gave importance to security of the regional
states and understood the Turkish security problems. But he
pointed out that the move taken by Turkey is not the solution to
the problem.
</P>
<P>
About 50,000-strong Turkish government troops have carried out
the cross-border military operations in northern Iraq since May
14 to wipe out the PKK rebels there.
</P>
<P>
Bourujerdi urged Turkey to immediately put an end to the
current operations in northern Iraq. 
</P>
