<HEADLINE> Chinese Insurance Company Cooperating With Swiss Giant </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The New China Life Insurance
Co. Ltd. is increasing cooperation with the Swiss Reinsurance
Company in technology, management, and personnel training.
</P>
<P>
New China Insurance, which was established last August, wrote
580 million yuan in life insurance premiums in the past ten months.
</P>
<P>
Sun Weiguang, its deputy general manager, said that it has
become one of the three major players in Beijing's life insurance
business, and will establish branch companies in major Chinese
cities this year.
</P>
<P>
John Coomber, a member of the Executive Board of Swiss
Reinsurance, said that he is quite confident in China's economic
growth, and in that of the insurance business.
</P>
<P>
Sun Bing, a general manager of New China Insurance, noted, "We
think this is a turning point for my company to seek development
in the world insurance market, by cooperating with 134-year-old
Swiss Reinsurance."
</P>
<P>
China has five big insurers: PICC Life, China Ping An Insurance
Co. Ltd, the Pacific Insurance Co. Ltd, New China Insurance
Co. Ltd, and Tai Kang Insurance.
</P>
<P>
It is estimated that China's life insurance companies will have
more than 100 billion yuan in premiums by the year 2000. 
</P>
