<HEADLINE> Chinese General Meets With Zimbabwe Army Commander </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- General Fu Quanyou, the chief of
the General Staff of the People's Liberation Army (PLA), in a
meeting with Zimbabwe's Army Commander C. G. Chiwenga here today,
said that frequent exchanges between military leaders of the two
countries will be conducive to developing friendship and
cooperation between their armed forces.
</P>
<P>
Fu said that China and Zimbabwe have a time-honored friendship,
and that bilateral cooperation in various spheres has been
satisfactory. China values friendship and cooperation between the
two armed forces, and is willing to increase these relations, he
added.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his appreciation for Zimbabwe's adhering to the
"one China" policy and its support for China on the human rights
issue.
</P>
<P>
He also briefed Chiwenga on China's domestic situation and on
army building.
</P>
<P>
Chiwenga said that the two countries have a profound
friendship, and he expressed his thanks to the Chinese government
and people for their help over the past several decades. He said
that the Zimbabwean government will continue to observe the "one
China" policy.
</P>
<P>
He also congratulated China on the upcoming return of Hong Kong
to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Xiong Guangkai, deputy chief of the PLA General Staff, also
attended the meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
