<HEADLINE> Tiger Captured Alive at Western Nepali Village </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Police in western Nepal captured
alive a tiger who strayed into a villager's house, the official
RSS news agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The rogue tiger wandered into a house at the village of the
Gulmi district, about 150 km west of Kathmandu, in the afternoon
last Wednesday. The villagers managed to lock it inside a room and
then informed the district administration of the incident.
</P>
<P>
A police team arrived and managed to capture the 3 feet long
and 2.5 feet tall tiger without any harm.
</P>
<P>
The tiger had been released into the wild by the local forest
office after the police submitted it to the office, the RSS said.
 
