<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Permits Joint-Venture Asset Evaluation Agencies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Overseas asset appraising agencies
are allowed to set up joint or cooperative ventures in China but
are barred from establishing solely-owned evaluation institutions,
according to official regulations released recently.
</P>
<P>
The provisional rules were jointly issued by the State
Administration of State Property (SASP) and the Ministry of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Overseas asset evaluation agencies are limited to set up one
venture each in China and their registered capital cannot be less
than 500,000 US dollars, the rules say.
</P>
<P>
The operation period of overseas-funded appraising agencies in
China cannot be longer than 30 years, the rules stipulate.
</P>
<P>
The officially approved overseas-funded asset evaluation
agencies are permitted to engage in appraising liquid assets,
assets of long-term investments, real estate, machinery and
equipment, projects under construction, and intangible assets,
according to the rules.
</P>
<P>
They also say that the establishment of overseas-funded asset
evaluation agencies must be approved by the departments for
foreign trade and economic cooperation at the provincial,
municipal and autonomous regional level and by concerned
departments of the State Council.
</P>
<P>
The qualifications and business scope of overseas-funded asset
evaluation agencies will examined and regulated by the SASP.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
