<HEADLINE> Share Prices Continue to Slip Lower on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Share prices continued to slip
lower in dull trading on the Singapore market as the benchmark
Straits Times Industrials Index fell by 2.09 points to close at
2,030.21 points today.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume shrank to 94.97 million units, valued
at 292.39 million Singapore dollars (about 204.47 million US
dollars). Declines continued to lead advances by 171 to 110, while
343 other counters remained steady.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Land was the most actively traded stock as it
registered a turnover of 8.33 million units. It was followed by
Westmont Land which had 4.89 million shares traded. JSH Warrant 98
was next with 4.73 million shares changed hands.
</P>
<P>
NBT led the gainers of the day as it rose by 1.6 dollars to
finish at 20.2 Singapore dollars. Bukit Sembawang and the United
Overseas Bank (UOB) Foreign gained 20 cents each to end at 28 and
16 Singapore dollars respectively. ANA (All-Nippon Airways) Hotels
and Shangri-la increased by 12 cents each to close at 3.6 and 4.22
dollars respectively.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, the Singapore Airlines Foreign was the biggest
loser as it declined by 30 cents to end at 12.3 Singapore dollars.
JMH 400 and the Thai Prime Fund fell by 25 cents each to close at
8.05 and 8.75 US dollars respectively. Creative 50 and the
Overseas Chinese Banking Corporation (OCBC) Foreign finished 20
cents lower at 23.1 and 15.2 Singapore dollars respectively.
</P>
</TEXT>
