<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shea Cake, New Effective Pesticide </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Shea cake, a toxic residue in Shea
oil extraction process, is an effective pesticide, a forestry
official in Lira District, northern Uganda has confirmed.
</P>
<P>
The cake can not be used as a feed to raise animals due to its
toxicity, but it is proved an environmently friendly substance in
fighting against termites and other pests on farms, "The New
Vision" reported today.
</P>
<P>
George Mabuya, the district forest officer, told the paper
that field trials of his department indicated the cake is a very
effective pesticide and the demand for the stuff is very high.
</P>
<P>
Shea tree is used as a material for charcoal making by local
people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
