<HEADLINE> India's Inflation Stays Steady at 6 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, June 9 (Xinhua) -- India' annual rate of inflation
remained the same at the previous week's level of 6 percent for
the week ending May 17, the Hindustan Times reported today.
</P>
<P>
The rate of inflation during the corresponding week of 1996 was
4.45 percent.
</P>
<P>
However, the official Wholesale Price Index for "all
commodities" (base 1981-82=100) moved up marginally by 0.1 percent
during the week under review to 323.5 from 323.3 the week before.
</P>
<P>
During the week under review, prices of commodities such as
nitric acid and poultry chicken witnessed sharp increases while
those of fodder and raw rubber eased substantially.  
