<HEADLINE> WFP Donates 9,550 Tons of Relief Food to Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The World Food Program (WFP)
has donated 9,550 tons of food aid to Tanzania to be distributed
in places facing acute food shortage, local press reported today.
</P>
<P>
Sources in the Prime Minister's Office told reporters here on
Sunday that the distribution of the relief food would start in
two weeks.
</P>
<P>
Available data indicated that about 189,583 people in Arusha,
Tabora, Singida, Mwanza, Dodoma, Lindi and some other regions
face acute food shortage at present.
</P>
<P>
The sources said that some 9,100 tons of maize and 450 tons of
beans, worth about 2.6 million US Dollars, would be distributed
freely to the elderly and those with poor health.
</P>
<P>
The WFP also provided about 1.1 million US Dollars to cover
distribution expenses, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
According to the sources, some non-governmental organizations
will help the government distribute the food. 
</P>
