<HEADLINE> Botswana's Economic Growth Tops 7 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Botswana recorded economic
growth last year of 7 percent compared to 3.1 percent in the
previous year, the country's Central Bank has announced.
</P>
<P>
The figures were released by the bank on Saturday in its
annual report, reports reaching here from Gaborone said.
</P>
<P>
The bank attributed what it termed "the robust real Gross
Domestic Products growth", the highest in the southern African
country, to booming diamond sales.
</P>
<P>
Diamond mining recorded a growth of 9.9 percent for the
financial year to March 31 mainly due to increased capacity at
Jwaneng Mine and to higher prices of gems.
</P>
<P>
The trade sector, the report said, recorded a 7.3 percent
growth rate, while manufacturing grew by 6.5 percent, up from 4.3
percent in 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
