<HEADLINE> Noted Playwright Dies at 90 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Yu Ling, one of China's pioneer
dramatists, died of illness at the age of 90 on June 7 in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The playwright was among a group to organize the country's "New
Arts Movement" led by the Chinese Communist Party in the 1930s,
and has devoted his life to the revolutionary cause.
</P>
<P>
Yu was a vice-chairman of the China Film Association and
president of the Shanghai Drama Institute.
</P>
<P>
A gifted artist, he has written some 60 dramas and screenplays,
among which some went on to become national classics.  
</P>
