<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Petrol price in Uganda went up
from 1,150 Shillings (about 1.0748 Dollars) to 1,170 Shillings
(about 1.0935 Dollars) per liter last week, reported local daily
"The New Vision" today.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time that petrol price started to rise in the
country.
</P>
<P>
In January this year, the petrol price per liter fell by as
much as 20 Shillings from December last year. In April, the price
of petrol fell to 1,150 Shillings from 1,160 Shillings per liter.
</P>
<P>
However, kerosene price went down last week to 830 Shillings
from 840 Shillings per liter while diesel remained at 1,030
Shillings a liter.
</P>
<P>
On the reason of Kerosene price reduction, the paper said that
it is a product of an appreciating Uganda Shilling against U.S.
Dollar, falling world fuel prices and a reduction in fuel duties
in the country.
</P>
<P>
However, the paper didn't give the reason for petrol price
rise. 
</P>
