<HEADLINE> Engineering Doctorate to be Conferred in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, June 9 (Xinhua) -- A Myanmar state technological
institute, Yangon Institute of Technology (YIT), will open the
first ever doctorate courses in engineering by the middle of this
month to nurture high-level technicians, local sources said.
</P>
<P>
The eventual opening of the courses of doctorate degree for the
1997-98 academic year signified that Myanmar students can soon
seek for higher degree in the engineering major at home instead of
getting it from abroad.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar students had to undergo further study in foreign
countries to acquire a doctorate degree in the major in the past.
</P>
<P>
According to a recent announcement of the Myanmar Ministry of
Science and Technology, the courses to be conducted will be
divided into five branches such as civil, mechanical, chemical,
petroleum and architectural engineering.
</P>
<P>
Students who have obtained the master degrees of its respective
branches will be allowed to join the courses on condition that
their parents are Myanmar citizens, the announcement said.
</P>
<P>
The YIT, together with the Mandalay Institute of Technology
(MIT), are among the 51 universities, colleges and institutes in
Myanmar.  
</P>
