could safely intrude into our airspace, safely landed, stayed and
took off without obstruction," said the former prime minister.
</P>
<P>
A press release issued by the Ministry of Foreign Affairs on
Sunday said an Indian Air Force helicopter landed at Chunarghat on
May 20, at 1815 hours (local time). The helicopter carried six
persons in uniform and one in civilian clothes.
</P>
<P>
"After they were told by the local people that the place they
had landed was inside Bangladesh, the helicopter took off at 1820
hours (local time) and flew eastward towards India," the release
said.
</P>
<P>
The Indian government was asked to investigate immediately the
reason for such violation, provide detailed information on the
helicopter and its crew and other passengers, and also ensure
prevention of recurrence of such incidents, the release added.
