<HEADLINE> Japan Becomes Major Investor In Dalian </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DALIAN, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Japan has become a major investor in
the coastal city of Dalian, regarded by some Japanese experts as
an ideal spot for investment with its convenient roadways and
sound infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
So far, over 1,400 Japanese-funded firms have been set up in
the city in northeastern Liaoning Province, with a total
investment of 3.18 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, 319 economic institutions of other types have been
established in Dalian by the Japanese. Dalian has been the second
largest recipient of Japanese investment in the country, following
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Many large Japanese companies have set foot in Dalian and a
number of Japanese cities have sealed sistership agreements with
the city.  
