<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Tunisia became the third World
Cup finalists from Africa with a 0-0 draw against Egypt in a North
African showdown on Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
The Tunisians needed a victory to have any chance of catching
the Group 2 pacesetters only to discover there was no way through
the visitors defence at the Nasser Stadium .
</P>
<P>
Tunisia have 13 points, six more than the Egyptians, making
their final match at home to bottom-of-the-table Namibia on August
16 of academic interest only.
</P>
<P>
Nigeria and Morocco reached the 1998 finals in France on
Saturday with contrasting home victories as the Super Eagles
trounced Kenya 3-0 while the Lions of the Atlas edged Ghana by a
solitary goal.
</P>
<P>
Cameroon boosted their hopes of filling one of the other two
places by drawing 1-1 in Angola to maintain a two-point advantage
at the top of Group 4.
</P>
<P>
The Indomitable Lions took a 50th-minute lead through Patrick
Mboma following good work by Bernard Tchoutang and Fabrice 'Akwa'
Maieco levelled soon after with his head.
</P>
<P>
Togo achieved their first victory in the same group beating
understrength Zimbabwe 2-1 in Lome through a couple of early goals
from German-based professional Bachirou Salou.
</P>
<P>
South Africa replaced Congo at the top of Group 3 on goal
difference following an impressive 3-0 triumph over Zambia while
the Red Devils defeated the Democratic Republic of Congo by a
solitary goal.
</P>
<P>
In other cup ties, Guinea came from behind to overcome Burkina
Faso 3-1 in Conakry while a late goal from Gervatius Uri-Khob gave
Namibia a shock 2-1 away win over George Weah-less Liberia.
</P>
