<HEADLINE> Jan Zelezny Wins Javelin at IAAF Grand Prix </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The 1996 Atlanta Olympic champion
and world record holder Jan Zelezny of the Czech Republic won the
javelin event at the IAAF Grand Prix athletics meeting here on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
On the windy and wet evening Zelezny threw 86.92m for the
title. while British Steve Backley managed 83.90m at the Znamensky
memorial tournament.
</P>
<P>
The Russian pole-vaulter Maxim Tarasov, who won the gold medal
in the 1992 Barcelona Olympics, failed to conquer Atlanta's
Olympic champion Jean Galfione of France. Galfione reached 5.80m
and finished first, while Tarasov was fifth with a dissapointing
5.60m.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was highlighted by Kenyan runners. William Tanui
clocked three minutes 36,87 seconds in the 3,000m -- the fastest
time in the world so far this year.
</P>
<P>
And in the men's 800m, David Kiptoo surged home in 1:44.57,.
</P>
<P>
In the 100m, Nigeria's Davidson Edzinva clocked 10.20 and
finished well ahead of Olympic and world champion Donovan Baily of
Canada (10.28) who placed second.
</P>
<P>
In the women's 400m Nigerian Bisi Afolabi set the season's best
result in 50.55, and in the 800m, Atlanta's double Olympic gold
medallist Svetlana Masterkova of Russia placed first with
1:59.86. 
</P>
