<HEADLINE> Bulgaria Beats Luxembourg in World Cup Qualifer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Bulgaria blanked Luxembourg 4-0 in
their European Zone World Cup Group five qualifier here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Hristo Stoichkov crowned his return from international exile
with one of the four goals at the match. The 31-year-old
Stoichkov, who changed his mind about not playing for the
national side unless Christo Bonev the coach was removed, netted a
43rd minute penalty after strike partner Emil Kostadinov had been
fouled.
