<HEADLINE> China Makes First Submarine for Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The first China-made sightseeing
submarine completed its trial voyage in Sanya, a city on Hainan
Island's south coast.
</P>
<P>
China is now one of a few countries that manufacture submarines
for sightseeing purposes, according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
The 43-seat "Hanglu No. 1" is 23.5 m long, has a displacement
of 125 tons and can go to a depth of 50 meters.
</P>
<P>
The vessel uses materials similar to those used for the
fuselage of the Boeing-737 for its passenger section, and carbon
dioxide-filters keep the air clean in it.
</P>
<P>
The under-water tours last for 50 minutes and will open to
tourists next month. 
</P>
</TEXT>
