<HEADLINE> Spain Beats Czech Republic in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, June 8 (Xinhua) -- A penalty by Fernando Hierro five
minutes before the break gave Group six pacesetters Spain a 1-0
win over the Czech Republic in a World Cup European Zone qualifier
in Valladolid, Spain on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Scottish referee High Dallas had no hesitation pointing to the
spot when Alfonso was brought crashing down by Czech goalkeeper
Srnicek and the Real Madrid marksman made no mistakes from the
spot.
</P>
<P>
The penalty came after Spain had dominated territorially in the
first-half -- although the visitors went close after half-an-hour
with a cleverly flighted Nedved free-kick which was plucked
spectacularly out of the air by Zubizarreta.
</P>
<P>
After the interval Spain settled back to defend their lead and
the Czechs with few ideas up front were unable to capitalise.
</P>
<P>
Spain are now unbeaten in eight matches with six wins and two
draws and are one point clear of Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
The Czech Republic are struggling with just one win from five
matches. 
</P>
</TEXT>
