<DOCNO> XIE19970609.0183 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Balance of Payments Surplus Down in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, June 9 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' balance of payments
(BOP) surplus dropped sharply during the first five months of this
year to 448 million US dollars, the local newspaper Business World
reported today.
</P>
<P>
Preliminary figures from the Philippine Central Bank showed
that this level is 77 percent less than the year-ago figure of
1.961 billion US dollars, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The BOP for May was based on the net international reserves of
the central bank as of May 31 at 10.037 billion which failed to
reach the planned target, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The central bank has targeted net international reserves at
11.323 billion US dollars for the previous months.
</P>
<P>
Figures from the bank indicated that the drop was due to debt
servicing requirements and the effect of the recent unloading of
greenbacks by the bank to defend the pesos from speculative
attacks.
</P>
<P>
The BOP records the country's transactions with other
countries. A BOP surplus means the country has more funds for
trade and investments coming in than it pays out to other
countries.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970609.0184 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> All Children From China's Smallest minority group Receive Education </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, June 9 (Xinhua) -- One hundred percent of school-age
children of the Hezhe nationality, the least populated of China's
55 minority groups, have enrolled in primary school in the past
few years.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, there have been quite a number of university and post
graduate students of the Hezhe, which before the founding of New
China in 1949 had only two students to complete primary school.
</P>
<P>
The Hezhe population has risen from 300 in 1949 to the current
4,000. Most of them live near the two banks of the Heilongjiang
River and the Wusuli River in northeast China's Heilongjiang
province.
</P>
<P>
The minority group has its own spoken language but no written
language.
</P>
<P>
The central government has provided special funding for the
development of education in the Hezhe-occupied region. Primary
schools have been built in all of the three counties that are home
to the nationality.
</P>
<P>
The state has been offering financial assistance for those
schools and giving each Hezhe student a small amount of aid each
year.
</P>
<P>
China has also established preferential policies for schooling
and employment of minority young people.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that more than a dozen Hezhes have received
higher education. Soem of them have become deputies to the
National People's Congress, government officials, engineers,
doctors, artists or teachers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
