<HEADLINE> Australia Wins Champions Trophy Women's Hockey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, June 8 (Xinhua) -- A golden goal from Alyson Annan in
extra-time gave Australia a 2-1 win over Germany, and take their
fourth consecutive Champions Trophy women's hockey title on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Anna, who started the final with a cracking shot that hit the
upright, finished off the Germans stern challenge seven minutes
and 16 seconds into sudden death extra-time.
</P>
<P>
She shuffled behind German goalkeeper Julia Zwehl, who had
played brilliantly in her first tournament, to score from Katrina
Powell's pass.
</P>
<P>
The Germans punished Annan's opening miss by taking the lead a
minute later through Britta Becker. Gill Clarke, the English
umpire celebrating her 100th game in charge, gave Germany the
advantage as Becker volleyed in.
</P>
<P>
German joy was short lived as Powell took advantage of a
hesitant German defence in the eighth minute to equalise.
</P>
<P>
In a thrilling seven goal bonanza, the Netherlands beat Olympic
silver medallists South Korea 5-2 in the third place match.
</P>
<P>
In the day's another match, Britain beat the United States 3-0
to record their second win in two days over a winless American
team. 
</P>
</TEXT>
