<HEADLINE> Boardman Wins Prologue at Criterium du Dauphine Cycling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 8 (Xinhua) -- British rider Chris Boardman, world
hour record holder, won the 5.1km prologue stage of the Criterium
du Dauphine in Grenoble, France on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 28-year-old Boardman, also the world pursuit champion,
clocked a winning time of five minutes 50.12 seconds, beating the
world time-trial champion Alex Zulle of Switzerland and Russian
Viacheslav Ekimov by three seconds.
</P>
<P>
The biggest loser of the day was Frenchman Richard Virenque,
three times King of the Mountains in the Tour de France, who lost
28 seconds. 
</P>
