<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ericsson to Produce SDH Equipment in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 9 (Xinhua) -- Sweden's Ericsson established a
joint venture in China to produce synchronous digital hierarchy
(SDH) broad-band network systems for the fast growing Chinese
telecoms market.
</P>
<P>
Wuhan Yangtze Ericsson Telecommunications Company was set up in
Wuhan, the capital of Hubei Province, with 10 million US dollars
in registered capital, jointly with Wuhan Research Institute under
the Ministry of Post and Telecommunications'.
</P>
<P>
When the joint venture starts operation this September, it will
make Ericsson the only foreign telecoms company in China with
joint ventures capable of providing a complete range of telecoms
products and services.
</P>
<P>
The Wuhan Research Institute is one of the country's major
suppliers of transmission and fiber-optic equipment. It began
cooperating with Ericsson when it signed a SDH technology
transfer agreement with the company in 1995.
</P>
<P>
China has now become the second largest market in the world,
after the US, for Ericsson's products. The company has invested
more than 100 million US dollars in China setting up 19
representative offices and nine joint ventures. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
