<HEADLINE> Gotti Wins Tour of Italy Cycling Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Italian rider Ivan Gotti defeated 1996
winner Pavel Tonkov of Russia to clinch the Tour of Italy on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Wih the victory, he become the first Italian victor in the race
since his Saeco team director Franco Chioccioli six years ago.
</P>
<P>
Italian Mario Cipollini captured the 22nd and final stage of
the race as 28-year-old Gotti finished with a one minute 27
seconds advantage over Tonkov in the overall standings.
</P>
<P>
Gotti had worn the leader's pink jersey since his fourth stage
victory in Cervinnia and successfully withstood repeated attacks
by Tonkov over the final days in the mountains.
</P>
<P>
Italy's Giuseppe Guerini was third overall, while Cipollini,
with five stage wins, took the points title and Colombia's Chepe
Gonzalez Pico was king of the mountains. 
</P>
</TEXT>
