<DOCNO> XIE19970609.0208 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-09 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Leader Meets Berlin Mayor </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BERLIN, June 8 (Xinhua) -- Visiting Chinese leader Li Ruihuan
met with Berlin Mayor Eberhard Diepgen here today, both expressing
the hope that friendly relations and cooperation between the two
sides will be further strengthened.
</P>
<P>
Li, chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), said during the meeting
that Berlin is both an ancient and modern metropolitan. As the
capital of the reunified Germany, it is now displaying its
vitality.
</P>
<P>
He also noted that as a city which has established sisterly
relationship with China's capital of Beijing, Berlin has played an
important role in the development of the friendly relations
between China and Germany.
</P>
<P>
Li also praised Diepgen as an old friend of the Chinese people,
who has made contributions to expanding relations between China
and Germany.
</P>
<P>
Diepgen said that Berlin and Beijing have been cooperating very
well and Berlin lays great emphasis on the relations between the
two capital cities.
</P>
<P>
Berlin is strong in technologies such as medical care and
environmental protection and hopes to strengthen its cooperation
with the Chinese side in these fields, he added.
</P>
<P>
Li, who is on a seven-day official goodwill visit to Germany,
arrived at Berlin from the southern German city of Munich on
Saturday. He will leave for Bonn Monday to continue his visit.
</P>
</TEXT>
